title: What to do about Evil?
Ask HN: What are household items that can be repaired but people often replace?
text:
My original question (but had to shorten): What are some common household items that are easy to repair but that people usually replace?

For example I often buy a new shower mat when it inevitably gets moldy and they're relatively cheap, but I appreciate I could clean it instead, which would be less wasteful.

Tell HN: Support chat turns on camera in Amazon app
text:
I received a gift from Amazon that I didn’t want, so I attempted to return it. Turned out to be “non-returnable” (food related), so I was directed to talk to support for a refund.

During that chat session, I noticed the iOS camera indicator was on. Pulling down the toolbar showed that it was the Amazon app. I went to my settings and disabled it, which cause the app to quit and lose my chat session.

I am shaken by the fact that they were probably watching me. This was a serious invasion of my privacy, and I didn’t even finish the refund process. How is this legal?

Ask HN: How do you search your Google MyActivity takeout HTML file
text:
I just downloaded my Google "MyActivity" takeout html file (it's a file of all your activity on Google and Chrome that you can download for yourself. It's an HTML file).

It was multiple hundreds of MB in size.

I opened it in Notepad++ and searched for "etymology". I'm an etymology junkie. And was amazed at how many word/phrase origins I had searched for that I couldn't even remember searching for.

The problem was that it was very very slow. I didn't expect Notepad++ to choke on such a large file, but it did. (It wouldn't open in Chrome, it froze Chrome.)

Any thoughts on what app I should open it in if all I want to do is text search?
